solution: ```class Solution {
    public int removePalindromeSub(String s) {
        if (s.isEmpty()) return 0;
        int l = 0, r = s.length() - 1;
        while (l < r) {
            if (s.charAt(l) != s.charAt(r)) return 2;
            l++; r--;
        }
        return 1;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Check if the entire string is a palindrome; if yes, one step suffices. Otherwise, two steps always work because all 'a's form one palindromic subsequence and all 'b's form another.

